{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-14",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_14_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "La Paloma",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 491.88,
  "page_end_sec": 733.72,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.72,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 491.88,
      "end": 493.54,
      "text": "\"But I got a hunch you ain't going"
    },
    {
      "start": 493.82,
      "end": 494.72,
      "text": "all the way with me."
    },
    {
      "start": 495.15,
      "end": 497.28,
      "text": "What's the honest-to-God on this guy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 497.38,
      "end": 497.62,
      "text": "Sam?"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.3,
      "end": 499.78,
      "text": "You don't have to kick back on me."
    },
    {
      "start": 500.26,
      "end": 501.34,
      "text": "You know I'm regular.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 502.592,
      "end": 504.56,
      "text": "Spade lifted his eyes from the silver dome.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 504.8,
      "end": 506.36,
      "text": "They were clear and candid."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.16,
      "end": 507.68,
      "text": "\"Sure, you are,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 507.82,
      "end": 508.34,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 508.56,
      "end": 509.96,
      "text": "\"I'm not holding out."
    },
    {
      "start": 510.5,
      "end": 511.64,
      "text": "I gave you it straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.46,
      "end": 513.62,
      "text": "I'm doing a job for him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 513.86,
      "end": 515.92,
      "text": "but he's got some friends that look wrong to me"
    },
    {
      "start": 516.0,
      "end": 517.56,
      "text": "and I'm a little leery of him.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 518.17,
      "end": 520.97,
      "text": "\"The kid we chased out yesterday was one of his friends.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 520.95,
      "end": 522.61,
      "text": "\"Yes, Luke, he was.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 522.99,
      "end": 524.23,
      "text": "\"And it was one of them"
    },
    {
      "start": 524.23,
      "end": 525.43,
      "text": "that shoved Miles across.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 526.35,
      "end": 527.53,
      "text": "Spade shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 528.23,
      "end": 529.47,
      "text": "\"Thursby killed Miles.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 529.85,
      "end": 531.05,
      "text": "\"And who killed him?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 531.63,
      "end": 532.35,
      "text": "Spade smiled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 533.23,
      "end": 535.99,
      "text": "*\"That's supposed to be a secret, but, confidentially, I",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 535.99,
      "end": 538.01,
      "text": "did,\" he said, \"according to the police.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 540.69,
      "end": 542.61,
      "text": "*\"You're a tough one to figure out, Sam.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 547.5,
      "end": 549.92,
      "text": "They stopped at the desk long enough",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 549.92,
      "end": 552.48,
      "text": "for Luke to \"fix it so we'll get a ring"
    },
    {
      "start": 553.44,
      "end": 554.86,
      "text": "if he comes in,\" and went up to Cairo's room."
    },
    {
      "start": 555.02,
      "end": 555.96,
      "text": "Cairo's bed was smooth and trim,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 555.96,
      "end": 556.68,
      "text": "the wastebasket,"
    },
    {
      "start": 556.84,
      "end": 558.58,
      "text": "unevenly drawn blinds,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.58,
      "end": 561.08,
      "text": "and a couple of rumpled towels in the bathroom showed"
    },
    {
      "start": 561.36,
      "end": 564.28,
      "text": "that the chambermaid had not yet been in that morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 565.344,
      "end": 567.12,
      "text": "Cairo's luggage consisted of a square"
    },
    {
      "start": 567.22,
      "end": 567.56,
      "text": "Cairo's luggage consisted of a square",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 567.66,
      "end": 568.5,
      "text": "a valise,"
    },
    {
      "start": 568.74,
      "end": 569.96,
      "text": "and a gladstone bag."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.0,
      "end": 573.08,
      "text": "His bathroom cabinet was stocked with cosmetics,"
    },
    {
      "start": 573.46,
      "end": 573.88,
      "text": "His bathroom-cabinet was stocked with cosmetics—"
    },
    {
      "start": 574.52,
      "end": 574.66,
      "text": "cans,"
    },
    {
      "start": 575.14,
      "end": 575.5,
      "text": "jars,"
    },
    {
      "start": 575.7,
      "end": 576.98,
      "text": "and bottles of powders,"
    },
    {
      "start": 577.04,
      "end": 577.54,
      "text": "creams,"
    },
    {
      "start": 577.92,
      "end": 578.72,
      "text": "unguents,"
    },
    {
      "start": 578.88,
      "end": 579.6,
      "text": "perfumes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 579.6,
      "end": 580.1,
      "text": "lotions,"
    },
    {
      "start": 580.12,
      "end": 580.78,
      "text": "and tonics."
    },
    {
      "start": 581.6,
      "end": 583.64,
      "text": "Two suits and an overcoat hung in the closet"
    },
    {
      "start": 583.64,
      "end": 585.84,
      "text": "Two suits and an overcoat hung in the closet",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 586.9,
      "end": 588.94,
      "text": "The valise and smaller bag were unlocked."
    },
    {
      "start": 589.88,
      "end": 592.12,
      "text": "The valise and smaller bag were unlocked.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 592.22,
      "end": 593.16,
      "text": "finished searching elsewhere."
    },
    {
      "start": 594.336,
      "end": 594.92,
      "text": "Blank so far,"
    },
    {
      "start": 595.14,
      "end": 595.72,
      "text": "\"Blank so far,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 595.9,
      "end": 597.76,
      "text": "as they dug down into the trunk."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.46,
      "end": 600.26,
      "text": "They found nothing there to interest them."
    },
    {
      "start": 601.14,
      "end": 603.38,
      "text": "They found nothing there to interest them.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 603.62,
      "end": 605.64,
      "text": "\"Any particular thing we're supposed to be looking for?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 606.06,
      "end": 607.04,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 607.88,
      "end": 609.79,
      "text": "\"No.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 610.88,
      "end": 611.88,
      "text": "He's supposed to have come here from Constantinople."
    },
    {
      "start": 612.08,
      "end": 614.68,
      "text": "I haven't seen anything that says he didn't."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.584,
      "end": 616.24,
      "text": "I haven't seen anything that says he didn't.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 617.248,
      "end": 618.14,
      "text": "\"What's his racket?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 618.43,
      "end": 620.26,
      "text": "Spade shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 621.24,
      "end": 623.44,
      "text": "\"That's something else I'd like to know.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 623.7,
      "end": 624.24,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 624.74,
      "end": 625.9,
      "text": "\"Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 626.56,
      "end": 628.4,
      "text": "this is our last shot.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 628.58,
      "end": 631.86,
      "text": "He took a newspaper from the basket.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 632.0,
      "end": 632.14,
      "text": "call."
    },
    {
      "start": 632.9,
      "end": 636.1,
      "text": "_Call_."
    },
    {
      "start": 636.88,
      "end": 637.54,
      "text": "It was folded with the classified-advertising-page outside."
    },
    {
      "start": 637.6,
      "end": 638.94,
      "text": "examined that page,"
    },
    {
      "start": 639.04,
      "end": 640.66,
      "text": "and nothing there stopped his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 641.36,
      "end": 643.66,
      "text": "He turned the paper over and looked at the page that had"
    },
    {
      "start": 643.66,
      "end": 644.54,
      "text": "He turned the paper over and looked at the page that had",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 645.42,
      "end": 647.58,
      "text": "the page that held financial and shipping news,"
    },
    {
      "start": 648.06,
      "end": 648.48,
      "text": "the weather,"
    },
    {
      "start": 648.64,
      "end": 649.24,
      "text": "births,"
    },
    {
      "start": 649.24,
      "end": 649.78,
      "text": "marriages,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.16,
      "end": 650.54,
      "text": "divorces,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.56,
      "end": 651.04,
      "text": "and deaths."
    },
    {
      "start": 651.39,
      "end": 653.28,
      "text": "From the lower left-hand corner,"
    },
    {
      "start": 653.44,
      "end": 655.18,
      "text": "From the lower left-hand corner,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 655.26,
      "end": 657.58,
      "text": "bottom of the second column had been torn out."
    },
    {
      "start": 658.656,
      "end": 660.68,
      "text": "Immediately above the tear was a small caption."
    },
    {
      "start": 660.44,
      "end": 660.98,
      "text": "*Immediately above the tear was a small caption _Arrived Today_ followed by:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 661.6,
      "end": 662.16,
      "text": "12:20 A. M.—Capac from Astoria."
    },
    {
      "start": 662.16,
      "end": 662.36,
      "text": "5:05 A. M.—Helen P. Drew from Greenwood."
    },
    {
      "start": 662.98,
      "end": 663.54,
      "text": "5:06 A. M.—Albarado from Bandon."
    },
    {
      "start": 676.58,
      "end": 677.14,
      "text": "The tear passed through the next line,"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.76,
      "end": 682.44,
      "text": "letters to make _from Sydney_ inferable."
    },
    {
      "start": 686.16,
      "end": 686.74,
      "text": "Spade put the _Call_ down on the desk and looked into the"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.33,
      "end": 689.46,
      "text": "He found a small piece of wrapping paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 689.68,
      "end": 690.8,
      "text": "He found a small piece of wrapping-paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 691.1,
      "end": 692.14,
      "text": "two hosiery"
    },
    {
      "start": 692.32,
      "end": 692.44,
      "text": "tags,"
    },
    {
      "start": 693.24,
      "end": 696.3,
      "text": "a haberdasher's sale ticket for half a dozen pairs of socks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 696.58,
      "end": 697.1,
      "text": "a haberdasher's sale-ticket for half a dozen pairs of socks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 697.2,
      "end": 698.76,
      "text": "in the bottom of the basket,"
    },
    {
      "start": 698.98,
      "end": 701.62,
      "text": "a piece of newspaper rolled into a tiny ball."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.74,
      "end": 703.9,
      "text": "He opened the ball carefully,"
    },
    {
      "start": 704.12,
      "end": 704.92,
      "text": "He opened the ball carefully,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 704.92,
      "end": 705.53,
      "text": "on the desk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.64,
      "end": 707.76,
      "text": "and fitted it into the torn part of the call."
    },
    {
      "start": 708.7,
      "end": 710.24,
      "text": "and fitted it into the torn part of the _Call_."
    },
    {
      "start": 710.8,
      "end": 712.18,
      "text": "The fit at the sides was exact,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 712.18,
      "end": 714.78,
      "text": "fragment and the inferable from Sidney half,"
    },
    {
      "start": 714.98,
      "end": 715.72,
      "text": "fragment and the inferable _from Sydney_ half,"
    },
    {
      "start": 715.86,
      "end": 716.18,
      "text": "missing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 716.26,
      "end": 718.72,
      "text": "sufficient space to have held announcement"
    },
    {
      "start": 718.72,
      "end": 720.32,
      "text": "of six or seven boats' arrival."
    },
    {
      "start": 721.46,
      "end": 721.9,
      "text": "He turned the"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.9,
      "end": 724.08,
      "text": "sheet over and saw that the other side of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 724.08,
      "end": 726.92,
      "text": "missing portion could have held only a meaningless"
    },
    {
      "start": 727.12,
      "end": 729.28,
      "text": "corner of a stock-broker's advertisement."
    },
    {
      "start": 730.28,
      "end": 730.48,
      "text": "Luke,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 730.68,
      "end": 731.86,
      "text": "Luke,"
    },
    {
      "start": 732.02,
      "end": 732.34,
      "text": "asked:"
    },
    {
      "start": 732.94,
      "end": 733.72,
      "text": "\"What's this all about?\""
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}